                    <comment id="12381473" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2004 10:31:19 +0000"  >Patch applied to 2.0.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This problem is a little more difficult in HEAD.  The socket timeout is set in HttpConnection.open() and &lt;br/&gt;
setSoTimeout() is deprecated.  Any preference on how we should handle this?  Here are a few quick &lt;br/&gt;
ideas that come to mind:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- un-deprecate setSoTimeout()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- add a method for synchronizing an HttpConnection with its params&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- remove support for changing a connection once opened&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- something else...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike</comment>
